_ _
__**Welcome to OE Midweek!**__
We’re excited to have you with us. In the following sections, you'll find relevant information for everything OE Midweek. Please reach out to one of the following if you have any questions.

Welcome to Occasional Excellence,  we're glad you’re here!

**The Officer Team**
> Babylonius - Guild Master
> Jake
> Kojiyama (Kartra)
> Zarantai
> Schlim
> Morgrom

Special Advisor
> Paoanii (Paninii/Casterdebuff)
_ _

embeds.title: Trialing with OE Midweek
embeds.description:
Trials aren’t rushed but take at least two full weeks during progression, and more during farm.  We like to take as long as it takes to decide if we are a good fit for each other.  Trials are treated as full members in every way and are allowed to roll on loot and use guild-provided flasks from cauldrons.

If you are looking for feedback on your trial, please reach out to an officer or anyone in the guild of your class/role.  All are more than happy to walk through logs with you and let you know where you might be able to improve your performance. 

Trials are expected to be on the server for the duration of their trial period. This is because the community is very important to us and we want you to be not only part of our raid but part of our wider guild community.  If you have extenuating circumstances that will delay your transfer to ~~Turalyon~~ **Area 52** by a week or more, please reach out.

~~**Turalyon is our home and it's a small server economically. Consider researching raiding materials costs to see if it is advantageous for you to bring over materials with you.**~~

*We're on Area 52 now.*

embeds.title: The Spreadsheet
embeds.description:
**[Raider Public Raidbook](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1frswwMADqiGDihLRL_DPBkWtUoSl4AAjO_8w5UMfmVU/edit#gid=440221849?usp=sharing)**

This Google Sheets book contains relevant information regarding raider boss needs, raid comps, boss progression rotations, and boss-specific assignments where necessary. Input what bosses you would like to be in for.  You will also find a tab for boss rotations. Raid comp is typically updated a few hours before the raid.  When farming, rotations are based on a combination of comp requirements and loot needs. 

Reach out to any of the officers if you have specific questions.

embeds.title: Looting Guidelines
embeds.description:
OE Midweek's looting system is LootCouncil. We take every precaution to make sure that loot is distributed in an equitable fashion that gives the most benefit to the *raid team*. Trinkets and Tier often be on a case-by-case basis.

Use notes anywhere you can to give Council a clear idea of how you intend to use the item. Keep non-productive notes to a minimum.
_ _

fields.name: *Armor*
fields.value:
__**Major**__
Any piece of armor that would be an upgrade of 1 “tier”of item level [Heroic to Mythic] (>=13 ilvl).
> In the event of tier pieces, any piece that would result in the completion of a bonus like 2pc or 4pc.

__**Minor**__
Any piece of armor that would be an upgrade of less than 1 tier of item level (<13 ilvl).
> In the event of tier pieces, any piece that would not result in the completion of a bonus like 1pc or 3pc.
> Any piece of gear that would be a stat 'sidegrade'.

__**Offspec & .Transmog**__
Self-Explanatory

fields.name: *Weapons and Trinkets*
fields.value:
__**Major**__
Main-hand upgrade of >=0.5 “tiers” of item level. [252 to 259] (>=6 ilvl)

__**Minor**__
An upgrade of < 0.5 “tiers” of item level (<6 ilvl).
> All off-hands.
> Stat "sidegrades"

__**Offspec & Transmog**__
Self-Explanatory

__**Trinkets**__
Trinkets are evaluated on a case-by-case basis because there is a disparate impact on which trinkets are "good" and whom they are desirable for. Try to follow the above guidelines as closely as possible, but trinket design tier over tier doesn't lend itself to easy systematic looting rules.

embeds.title: Attendance Policy
embeds.description: We ask that raiders update attendance as far in advance as possible to help prepare for comp. To do so, please post in the #oem-attendance channel of Discord. We are an adult guild and understand that circumstances may result in missing raid last minute.  If this happens, be sure to post in the Attendance channel in Discord AND message Babylonius so that we can adjust comp accordingly.  Note that excessive absences and/or multiple last-minute call-outs may result in removal from the team.

embeds.title: The Alt Code
embeds.description:
**Alts are brought to raid on a case-by-case basis.**
> *Alts are not made equal - different skills, different roles, different applications, different commitments. We have to make decisions in the best interest of the team and our time raiding.* 
**Alts should serve a fundamental purpose for the team.**
> __*Main swaps and re-rolls for comp reasons are one the biggest ways that we can increase the strength of our team when facing new, challenging content. We make exceptions to fulfill these situations where we need to.*__
**We will not guarantee GV tier unlocks for mains and alts simultaneously.**
> *Raid comp Tetris is fun for approximately 2 weeks, and then it's not fun any more. Too often these fights just don't allow for a lot of variability in our class and player comps. If the paradigm of 3/6/9 GV is maintained through SL, the most we will make an effort to accommodate is 3x for main, 3x for alt.*
**Alts cannot be a detriment to the raid - both in Progression and Farm.**
> *We get it, alts are...well... alts for a reason. We don't expect 90+ percentile parses, but we do expect a minimum of Blue-level output performance, high survivability, and upward trajectory of overall performance of your alt. We don't require alts, so if you are going to have one and you're not making the effort, then neither is Leadership.*
**Alts are held to the same standard as your main.**
> *There is really no way around this. Our common commodity is time, don't waste it.*
**Alts are not beyond redemption.**
> *Sometimes, alts come in and just suck. It happens. If you find yourself in a place where your alt is in Alt Jail, give yourself an opportunity to get better at that alt, gather some data, and make your case to Leadership again.*

fields.value:
1. Phase 1 (80%) <Reference timestamp>
2. Phase 2 (gauntlet) <Reference timestamp>
3. Phase 3

embeds.title: Phase 1 Strategy Notes
embeds.description:
1. Barbed Arrow will randomly stack on players. This is a heavy dot with an infinite duration that stacks; think Kaal bleeds.
2. Domination Arrows always chain to the closest person. Getting chained clears your Barbed Arrow bleed. We may need to use this to manage the dot, may not. On testing barbed arrow did not stack fast enough for this to matter.
3. Veil of Darkness (the huge black circle) won’t kill you when you get hit, but if multiple people get clipped by it, the debuff will spread and cause massive healing problems. This can wipe us very fast and comes ~15s after chains spawn.
4. You cannot melee your own domination arrow, if you get in melee range of it you will be instantly killed. You can melee anyone else’s arrow. This is important for the intermission at the end of p1 when everyone will get chained
5. The tankbuster is unique on this fight. If she has 3 or more stacks of Heartseeker, she replaces her next auto attack with a tankbuster. This is annoyingly inconsistent.
6. The arena is huge and wailing arrow’s falloff radius is similar to xymox bomb. Tanks don’t go too far with this or you’ll cause range issues.
7. When the boss hits 80% we’ll get an intermission where every player is chained and the boss launches huge massacre style lines. She will also cast a Banshee wail which does damage based on missing HP and splashes within 5 yards, so some big throughput CDs will be saved for this phase.

fields.name: Failure Points
fields.value:
Spreading Veil of Darkness
Getting pulled into your chain
Not killing chains fast enough

fields.name: Goals
fields.value: Don’t push with chains alive

embeds.title: Phase 2 Strategy Notes
embeds.description:
Priority 1 - Souljudge - Crushing Dread does increasing damage over time, dispel jumps to a new target and resets stacks (removed on mob death).
Priority 2 - Summoner - Summons 4 orbs that amp enemy damage every 6 seconds and minor explosion on death. Also have a moderate damage Curse that extends for every cast (stop casting or decurse)
Priority 3 - Goliath - Damage/attack speed increase per melee (reset on new target like Hungering)
(minor) Vanguard - does a minor melee impact (don’t tank on ranged)
(minor) Hopebreaker - Does a channel (stun/grip)

fields.name: Platform Set 1
fields.value:
1. Start with Jaina Bridge and dodging waves while we cross
2. Continue running+dodging across first chain platform
3. After some RP, Thrall spawns a bridge. 10 seconds later she starts to cast ruin, which is a 5 sec cast that will instant wipe if not kicked.

fields.name: 1st Burn
fields.value:
4. On this platform we dps Sylvanas from 84% to ~80%. She will continue to do Shadow Daggers and Veil of Darkness (see p1)
5. At 75.5% she will cast a Banshee Wail. We need to spread on the chain platform for this and be topped off.
6. There will be some RP while thrall spawns a bridge to a platform with adds.

fields.name: Platform Set 2
fields.value: 7. Platform 1 will have a Souljudge and a Goliath with multiple small adds. We have 30 seconds to clean up the adds and spawn a new bridge or we will wipe to ruin. There will be Veil of Night casts to dodge on this platform.

fields.name: 2nd Burn
fields.value:
8. After all the adds are dead, Jaina will spawn a bridge which we again have 15 seconds to cross and kick. If we don’t kill the adds within 40s, Sylv will cast Ruin whether a bridge is spawned or not and wipe us.
9. Platform 2 will have a Summoner and a Goliath with small adds. The same 30s limit applies here. We will get a Veil of Night on this platform.
10. Once the adds on platform 2 are dead, but before crossing the bridge, sylvanas will cast a banshee wail, which we need to spread for. After that cast we will cross and kick again.

fields.name: Clean Up
fields.value:
11. Platform 3 (final) has Souljudge and a Summoner with small adds. This platform is the hardest of the 3. We will get a veil of night with orbs from the summoner as well as Crushing Dread from the souljudge. We will use big raid CDs here. The same 30s timer applies from earlier platforms.
12. We cross another bridge and kick. We couldn’t find videos/logs beyond this point which weren’t bugged so after this is unknown.

fields.name: Failure Points
fields.value:
Spreading Veil of Darkness
Getting hit by Haunting Wave

fields.name: Goals
fields.value: Don't Die

embeds.title: Phase 3 Strategy Notes
embeds.description:
**__WE ARE NOT JUMPING TO OTHER PLATFORMS TO DEAL WITH MECHANICS__**

__1. Veil of Darkness (the black circle) will spawn on and follow two players. They cannot dodge it (might be able to immune/turtle it?), but everyone around them SHOULD dodge it. So if you are targeted by Veil of Darkness, stand still until you're hit by it. Once the debuff goes out, you will need to move into the raid group to survive Wailing Arrow, so spreading this in P3 is unavoidable.__

2. The tankbuster in this phase behaves the same as p1, except stacks are permanent and dispellable. Being dispelled drops a puddle that can be picked up by running into it again. Tanks will have to control these to minimize space usage.

3.  For Wailing Arrow, the raid will stack in the corner closest to the center platform, while the 3 targets will go to each other corner (first targetted goes left, 2nd targeted goes middle, 3rd targeted goes right).

fields.name: Ability Order Per Platform
fields.value:
1. Bane Arrows (dodge)
2. Shadow Dagger (dodge)
3. Banshee's Scream x2 - 5 seconds apart (spread and STAY SPREAD until Veil of Darkness is out)
4. Veil of Darkness
5. Wailing Arrow x3 staggered
6. Shadow Dagger (dodge)
7. Bane Arrows (dodge)
8. Banshee's Fury (dispel stacks)
9. Raze

fields.name: Failure Points
fields.value:
- getting hit by Veil of Darkness if you're not targeted (spreading is intended on the two targets hit).
- Having lots of stacks of Banshee’s Bane during Banshee’s Fury
- Cleaving Banshee’s Scream

fields.name: Goals
fields.value: 1. Manage Banshees Bane pools well

fields.value: Rings that come from outside or middle, use wormhole/immunities/door of shadows to cross. Turtle did not work, blink/nightfae is very hard to cross (similar to Eye of the Jailer beams)

fields.name: Fracturing Rift Blasts
fields.value: Similar to Castle Nathria, long beams targeted on players.

fields.name: Wormholes
fields.value: Similar function to Castle Nathria, Portal drop locations are pictured above. Used to cross to the platforms on mythic difficulty.

fields.name: Stasis Trap
fields.value: Similar to Castle Nathria, except they will re-arm immediately upon triggering this time. Immunities do not clear them. Targeted on Players and need to be baited well to keep floor space clear.

fields.name: Hyperlight Sparknova
fields.value: Similar to Castle Nathria, except it has a 3 yd splash now. Need to spread before each set of these.

fields.name: Glyph of Relocation
fields.value: Tank Debuff, pulls the entire raid to the tank when it expires. Make sure you are safe to get pulled in before this goes off because it can pull you through portals/traps. Often paired with Glyph of Relocation, so quick spread after the pull in.

fields.name: Platforms ___***MYTHIC ONLY***___
fields.value: During each phase, adds will spawn on one of the three platforms around the room. Raid will need to use the Wormholes dropped by using a warlock gateway to cross. Kill the adds and return to the main platform before the Forerunner rings and the platform collapse.

embeds.title: Intermission
embeds.description:
Adds will spawn. Priority is Acolyte > Spellslingers
Acolytes have a large frontal cone and transform and do a large pulsing AoE if not killed fast enough. 
Spellslingers will need to be interrupted or stunned.

fields.name: Ephemera Dust
fields.value: Debuff applied by all of Skolex's abilities, stacks and cannot be removed by immunes. Removed when forcing a burrow, but increases boss damage for the rest of the fight.

fields.name: Dust Blast
fields.value: Single targeted splash damage on the farthest three players from Skolex. Needs to be baited by three spread players and applies Ephemera Dust. Will be groups of ranged/healers rotating to bait this.

fields.name: Retch
fields.value: Large frontal cone targeted on a random player, if hit, deals a large amount of damage, stuns, and teleports the player to a random location.

fields.name: Volatile Residue ___***MYTHIC ONLY***___
fields.value: Players hit by puddles or frontals will leave a blue puddle on the ground for the rest of the fight.

fields.name: Devouring Blood ___***MYTHIC ONLY***___
fields.value: Skolex throws out puddles, if they hit a player they become permanent and reduce that players haste by 33% for 18 seconds as well as a heavy dot.

fields.name: Rend/Riftmaw
fields.value: Tank combo with a large frontal cone, similar to Aggramar/Shad'har/Guardian tank combo.

fields.name: Ravening Burrow
fields.value: Entire raid stacks, Boss will burrow. Dodge the blue circle, stay in the brown circle. Resets debuffs, but buffs boss damage.

embeds.description: Typical Council Fight, WAYYY TOO MANY ABILITIES.

fields.name: Phase Timestamps
fields.value:
P1: War (Interrupt Gloom Bolt) & Duty until one reaches 50%
P2: Renewal (Interrupt Anima Bolt) & Absolution until one reaches 50%
P3: All four.

fields.name: References
fields.value:
Heroic PTR Testing: <https://youtu.be/nIXWFev24_w>
Mythic PTR Testing: <https://youtu.be/7QzQ4-J5F7c>
Heroic PTR Log: <https://www.warcraftlogs.com/reports/TrMA63qGChmfwXjN#fight=last&type=damage-done&by=target>

fields.name: Necrotic Ritual
fields.value:
Adds spawn, 100% healing reduction aura until all adds are dead. A puddle will grow from the middle of the room until the adds die. 
Spawn Timings: 0:10, 1:10
***MYTHIC***  Night Hunters will happen in P1, each of the ritualists will need to be hit by one to break the shield on it.

fields.name: Runecarver's Deathtouch
fields.value: Debuff that does a large damage splash when dispelled. Target of this debuff needs to be in a Bastion's ward when dispelled.

fields.name: Ascension's Call/Bastion's Ward
fields.value: AMZ looking bubble. Players with the Runecarver's Deathtouch debuff must be inside when dispelled.

fields.name: Windswept Wings/Pinning Volley
fields.value: Boss will jump to the front of the room, and push back all players for 12 seconds. During the volley, spears will fall to targeted locations. If a player is hit by those spears they will be impaled and the spear will have to be killed to free them.

fields.name: Burden of Sin
fields.value: Debuff, players will gain an extra stack if hit by sinful projection.

fields.name: Sinful Projection
fields.value: Short debuff. When the debuff fades, 4 lines will shoot out from the player similar to the Prideful affix from S1 M+.

fields.name: Hand of Destruction
fields.value: All players get gripped to the boss, and that position will explode 6 seconds later. Damage taken from the explosion is distance based.

fields.name: Night Hunters
fields.value:
Same ability from Castle Nathria. Players need to soak the lines to split damage. 
***MYTHIC***  Needs to be ran through the ritualists to break shields.

fields.name: Wild Stampede
fields.value: Line of beasts that cross through the entire platform and knockback if hit.

fields.name: Withering Seeds
fields.value: Need to be healed to full. Once healed to 100%, the seed will give the raid a stacking buff that increases healing by 25% for 30 seconds, this buff stacks and can be chained.

fields.name: Animastorm
fields.value: Large tornadoes that move across the platform, large damage and silence if hit.

fields.name: Everything above
fields.value: Lust and burn. All bosses must die within 20 seconds of each other.

fields.name: Blasphemy
fields.value: Similar to Star Augar symbols. Spread prior to this mechanic, several players will get purple/yellow marks above their head. Run to a player with the opposite color without running over other players.

fields.name: Befouled Barrier
fields.value: Large yellow barrier, players stand inside and 75% of the healing done to those players goes into the shield. Any remaining shield after 25 seconds is applied to all players as a healing absorb.

fields.name: Wicked Star
fields.value: Three players are marked and have a star shot at them. Stars will shoot out from Anduin and then return, they deal a large amount of damage and silence. If adds are hit by a star, they become immune to interrupts and heal.

fields.name: Kingsmourne Hungers
fields.value: Ground AoE. Half of the raid will jump into each one to be sent to the other phase.

fields.name: Soul Phase
fields.value: Group, CC, and kill adds before they reach the middle. Focus small adds until the large add is at 30%, turn and burn. Heal the souls walking towards the middle.

embeds.title: Intermission
embeds.description: Focus Remnant of the Fallen King, cleave the other small adds.

fields.name: Monstrous Soul
fields.value: Turn and focus when it reaches 35%.

fields.name: Grim Reflections
fields.value: Replaces Blasphemy. Small adds that will chain cast a fear. Need to be interrupted or CC'd and killed. Adds will enrage if alive when boss transitions

embeds.title: Intermission
embeds.description: Focus Remnant of the Fallen King, cleave the other small adds.

fields.name: March of the Damned
fields.value: Wall of ghosts that walk across the platform and need to be dodged. Players hit are stunned and receive a dot.

fields.name: Hopelessness
fields.value: Everyone will receive a 30 second debuff. Only way to remove this is to run into the light zone in the middle of the arena. Triggering the bomb will one shot the player. Running into another player also triggers the bomb. Light zone will shrink every time a bomb is removed.
